#!   BEGIN_PYTHON=""
#!   BEGIN_TCL=""
#!   CATEGORY="FGP_TOOLS"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador (NL)&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;P_T_ABBR: Two letter abbreviation code of the province or terrirtory (ex.: ON, QC, ...).&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\LOG\QC.log&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\XLS&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\Data\PT_Harvester\QC\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;"
#!   DESTINATION="NONE"
#!   DESTINATION_ROUTING_FILE=""
